# Logging Convention

Always use the project logger from `helper/logger.js`. Do not use `console.log`, `console.error`, etc.

```javascript
// ❌ BAD
console.log('Processing user:', userId);
console.error('Failed to save:', error);

// ✅ GOOD - Use the default logger instance
const { logger } = require('../helper/logger');

logger.info('Processing user', { userId });
logger.error('Failed to save', { error });

// ✅ GOOD - Create a prefixed logger for better tracing
const { createLogger } = require('../helper/logger');
const logger = createLogger('myModule');

logger.info('Processing user', { userId });
logger.debug('Details', { data });
```

Adjust the require path based on the file's location relative to `helper/logger.js`.
